ess than it reinvented political institutions. She describes the colonial households that nurtured future revolutionaries, follows the development of political and family values during the revolutionary years, and shines new light on the radically transformed world that was inherited by nineteenth-century descendants. Beautifully written and replete with fascinating detail, this groundbreaking book is the first to introduce us to the founders as fathers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Apr 2020) 0aFounding Fathers of the United StatesvBiography. 0aFounding Fathers of the United StatesxFamily relationships. 7aHISTORY / United States / Revolutionary Period (1775-1800).2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300210750423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300210750.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO